Name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 2
Definition: A mitochondrial metabolism disease characterized by motor disability

Name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 1
Definition: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency characterized by onset at birth of lactic acidosis

Definition: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the UQCRB gene on chromosome 8q22.

Name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 4
Definition: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the UQCRQ gene on chromosome 5q31.

Name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 5
Definition: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency characterized by neonatal onset of severe metabolic acidosis associated with hyperammonemia and hypoglycemia and that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the UQCRC2 gene on chromosome 16p12.

Name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 6
Definition: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency characterized by onset in early childhood of episodic acute lactic acidosis

Name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 7
Definition: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the UQCC2 gene on chromosome 6p21.

Name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 8
Definition: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency characterized by childhood onset of progressive neurodegeneration that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the LYRM7 gene on chromosome 5q23.

Name: mitochondrial complex III deficiency nuclear type 9
Definition: A mitochondrial complex III deficiency that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the UQCC3 gene on chromosome 11q12.
